---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import BottomCTA from '../components/BottomCTA.astro';

const aboutSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'AboutPage',
  mainEntity: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: 'Jaiah Kamara',
    jobTitle: 'Founder',
    worksFor: {
      '@type': 'Organization',
      name: 'Signal to Summit',
    },
    description: '10 years at Best Buy in measurement and analytics. 7 of those years building Best Buy\'s retail media measurement infrastructure.',
    image: 'https://signaltosummit.com/images/jaiah-kamara-headshot-original.png',
    alumniOf: [
      { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'Best Buy Ads' },
      { '@type': 'EducationalOrganization', name: 'MIT UPRO AI Leadership Program' },
    ],
    knowsAbout: ['Retail Media', 'Platform Strategy', 'Coalition Dynamics', 'Measurement Infrastructure'],
  },
};
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="Jaiah Kamara spent 10 years at Best Buy in measurement and analytics, including 7 years building Best Buy's retail media measurement infrastructure. Signal to Summit brings operator-level insight to platform providers."
  schema={aboutSchema}
>
  {/* ── Section 2.1: OPENING FRAME ── */}
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-[45rem] px-6">
      <div class="md:flex md:items-start md:gap-12">
        <div class="md:flex-1">
          <h1 class="text-summit-navy mb-4">
            I spent seven years watching platform providers lose deals they should have won.
          </h1>
          <p class="text-summit-navy/70 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
            Not because their products failed — but because nobody diagnosed what was happening inside the retailer.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8 md:mt-0 md:flex-shrink-0 text-center">
          <img
            src="/images/jaiah-kamara-headshot-original.png"
            alt="Jaiah Kamara, Founder of Signal to Summit"
            class="w-56 md:w-72 rounded-lg object-cover aspect-[3/4]"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <p class="text-summit-navy font-semibold text-base mt-4">Jaiah Kamara</p>
          <p class="text-summit-navy/60 text-sm">Founder</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ── Section 2.2: THE CREDIBILITY STACK ── */}
  <Section background="soft-gray">
    {/* Paragraph 1 — The Operator Story */}
    <p class="text-summit-navy/90 leading-relaxed mb-10">
      I spent 10 years at Best Buy in measurement and analytics — building reporting teams, partnering with advertisers, and aligning product, analytics, engineering, and go-to-market functions across complex organizations. Seven of those years were spent building the measurement infrastructure for Best Buy Ads, one of the earliest retail media networks in the country.
    </p>

    {/* Paragraph 2 — The Diagnostic Lens */}
    <p class="text-summit-navy/90 leading-relaxed mb-10">
      What I saw, repeatedly, was the same pattern: platform providers with strong technology losing deals because they misread what was actually happening inside the retailer. Coalition dynamics that kill adoption before it starts. Delivery models that quietly become manual service businesses. Adoption timelines that stall — not because the retailer lacks interest, but because the platform never accounted for what implementation actually requires inside a complex organization.
    </p>

    {/* Paragraph 3 — The Advisory Stance */}
    <p class="text-summit-navy/90 leading-relaxed">
      Today I work with senior leaders at retail media enablement companies navigating these exact challenges. I don't nod along. I diagnose what's actually happening in the room you're trying to sell into — and I help you build a strategy that accounts for the operating reality your customers live with, not the one your roadmap assumes.
    </p>
  </Section>

  {/* ── Section 2.3: CREDENTIALS ── */}
  <Section>
    <p class="text-summit-navy/80 text-base leading-relaxed">
      Currently completing the MIT xPRO AI Leadership Program. Creator of Summit Signals — ongoing analysis of why retail media partnerships fail and how platform leaders can read the signals before deals stall.
    </p>
  </Section>

  {/* ── Section 2.4: PHILOSOPHY ── */}
  <Section background="soft-gray">
    <p class="text-summit-navy/90 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Grounded in servant leadership, systems thinking, and narrative precision. The work is straightforward: help platform providers close the gap between what their products can do and what their customers' organizations can actually absorb.
    </p>
  </Section>

  {/* ── Section 2.5: CTA ── */}
  <BottomCTA heading="If this sounds like the perspective you need, let's talk." />
</PageLayout>
